                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Louisville Ky</placeName>, <date>November 9<hi\n                        rend=\"sup\">th</hi> 1862</date></p>\n            <p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n                <placeName>Pha</placeName>!</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Revd and Dear Sir!</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(4)\">You will please to forward to <persName>Mr.<lb/> N.\n                Bloom</persName>, care of <persName>E. Bamberger &amp; Bloom</persName>, 3 copies of\n                all the<lb/> religious books used in your Sunday or Sabbath School, or per<lb/>haps\n                in your Educational Society School. I have established a<lb/> Sabbath School,\n                assisted by <persName>Mrs. N. Bloom</persName>; <persName>Abm Gerstle</persName>,\n                    <persName>Louis Dembity</persName> &amp;<lb/>\n                <persName>Dr. H. Filsenheld</persName>; <persName>Mrs. Dembity</persName> and\n                    <persName>Miss Sophie Bamberger</persName> also<lb/> offered their kind\n                services, and we desire to have books adapted<lb/> to the capacity and comprehension\n                of pupils from 6 to 15 years.<lb/> On the two last <date>Sabbaths</date> we had the\n                pleasure to be visited<lb/> by about 250 young ones, all eager to imbibe the\n                lessons<lb/> and truths of our time-honored faith. The books you send<lb/> will be\n                paid for by return of mail, and we may afterwards<lb/> order a number for each\n                pupil. If you should possess, or<lb/> could procure, a guide for post-biblical\n                history, adapted for<lb/> scholars of higher classes, or even self-instruction, I\n                would<lb/> be thankful to you, by sending several copies along with<lb/> the\n                others.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">You are no doubt aware, that there is a movement<lb/> on hand in my\n                congregation, to engage a Rabbi &amp; Preacher.<lb/> That it will affect my future\n                to a more or less extent, is sure.<lb/> There is, how-ever, a majority of members\n                opposed to these procee<lb/>dings, and it will remain a difficult task for the\n                money'd<lb/> minority to accomplish their designs. They speak of <persName>Dr.\n                    Deutsch</persName></p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3cr5nz7p/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
