                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3cr5nz7p/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>formerly of <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>; rumors, how-ever, are much<lb/>\n                against him, and, I think, even if he comes here on trial,<lb/> his election will be\n                defeated. Please to let me know,<lb/> if you choose, how his standing was in your\n                City, and what<lb/> are his religious principles as a Rabbi. If report speaks<lb/>\n                the truth, my congregation is not yet so much reformed, or<lb/> rather deformed, as\n                to digest a Rabbi with such radical<lb/> views.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Please to forward the mentioned books <sic>immediatly</sic>.<lb/>\n                Hoping and praying that you are well yet and zealous and<lb/> vigorous as ever I\n                subscribe myself</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(5)\">most Respectfully</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(6)\">yours</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(5)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">B. H. Gotthelf</persName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(5)\">\n                <date>11-9-1862</date>\n            </p>\n            <div>\n                <p>\n                    <ref target=\"Occident_PDFs/Occ_20_9.pdf\">The above text refers to Occident\n                        Volume 20 No. 9 page 429. Click here to view.</ref>\n                </p>\n            </div>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
